The paper deals with multi-item auctions, which are a classic topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of simple mechanisms, which are often used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economics (cs.EC). The smoothed analysis technique used in the paper is a common tool in theoretical computer science (cs.IT).
